Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Brotherhood
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 18
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,===============================================================

Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.55,0:01:34.14,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Resembool! We're in Resembool!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.58,0:01:42.30,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So what exactly are the Colonel's orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.30,0:01:45.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you tell me already, Major?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.25,0:01:47.76,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know many of the details, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.16,0:01:52.27,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I was simply told to bring you along to Resembool to meet up with the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.10,0:01:55.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Meet up with who?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.95,0:01:59.22,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Good day, Major Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.89,0:02:00.91,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.91,0:02:02.47,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.33,0:02:05.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Second Lieutenant Breda?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.81,0:02:14.48,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother should have arrived in Resembool a while ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.94,0:02:16.64,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,...but he still hasn't called...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.64,0:02:19.99,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, I'm here if he needs to have his arm repaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.26,0:02:24.19,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There's so much we don't know,\Nincluding Second Lieutenant Ross' case...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.19,0:02:26.18,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why I'm here to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.25,0:02:33.96,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,S-Since when?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.96,0:02:35.79,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you even come in from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.79,0:02:36.74,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,The window.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.66,0:02:40.51,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,I'm technically a criminal, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.50,0:02:46.77,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you guys don't need to worry about Edward.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.99,0:02:49.31,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, he's probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.77,0:02:52.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.48,0:03:01.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That damn Colonel... he didn't mention a word about us having to leave the country...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.86,0:03:06.20,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Han, are we almost there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.20,0:03:08.00,Default,Han,0000,0000,0000,,We've been here for a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.00,0:03:10.29,Default,Han,0000,0000,0000,,See? The Xerxes ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:24.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,340)}Whew~
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.01,0:03:28.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,0)}I almost burned myself with my automail...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.83,0:03:30.84,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,Why is the brat with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.84,0:03:32.52,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,For certain reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.34,0:03:38.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Xerxes, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.26,0:03:40.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I remember reading about it in\Nthe tale about the Sage of the East.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.89,0:03:42.67,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,Sage of the East?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.67,0:03:43.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.69,0:03:47.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A fairy tale about the alchemist who introduced alchemy to our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:03:52.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's a legend about the sole survivor of the\NXerxes Kingdom, which was destroyed in one night,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.82,0:03:59.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,and how he arrived in Amestris, just recently founded\Nat that time, and spread alchemy throughout the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.91,0:04:05.04,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,In our country, there's a legend stating he arrived from the west.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.77,0:04:11.93,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,Eastern alchemy as we know it today is a combination of the skills he brought us and Xing's technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.39,0:04:15.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the one developed as a method of healing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.56,0:04:16.81,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.52,0:04:21.45,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,We refer to him with respect,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.00,0:04:23.57,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,as the "Sage of the West".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.29,0:04:28.27,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,And this is where that sage was from?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.27,0:04:30.11,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,That's what's been told.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:31.66,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.70,0:04:35.33,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to see the Xerxes ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.93,0:04:38.84,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see why...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.14,0:04:45.88,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,But I wonder if it's truly possible for them to be destroyed in one night despite having advanced technology like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.88,0:04:48.39,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,It could just be a legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.47,0:05:00.72,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.72,0:05:01.74,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.59,0:05:22.16,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're going in pretty deep, aren't we...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.53,0:05:23.61,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Edward!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.97,0:05:32.43,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Eastern Headquarters, where I used to be stationed, was great. {ep 17}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.97,0:05:37.63,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It lacks the bustle of large cities,\Nand most of all, there are so many beauties. {ep 17}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.32,0:05:42.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That stupid colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.48,0:05:46.74,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Second Lieutenant Ross!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.89,0:05:50.62,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Now, for the embrace of reunion!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.62,0:05:51.74,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.94,0:05:52.64,Default-alt,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Second Lieutenant Ross!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.64,0:05:58.57,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,There's no telling when we'd get caught if a dead person was walking around the country, so we had her flee.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.57,0:06:02.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So the Colonel knew all along\NSecond Lieutenant Ross was innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.46,0:06:09.48,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think you're being a bit too flashy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.48,0:06:11.31,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You think so, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.31,0:06:12.14,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.86,0:06:14.90,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Hauling her down to the police station in front of a crowd...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.90,0:06:19.53,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Murdering a colleague is an embarrassment to the military, and yet, to have it make headlines...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.68,0:06:26.90,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.90,0:06:29.81,Default,TEL,0000,0000,0000,,A call from Warrant Officer Falman on a general line, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.81,0:06:30.53,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Put it through.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.29,0:06:34.01,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel! About the murder of Brigadier General Hughes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.01,0:06:36.64,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,Hey Falman! Let me talk to him for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.64,0:06:37.54,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Barry?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.21,0:06:40.88,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Mr. Mustang! Did you see the paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.88,0:06:42.38,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,I've got something interesting to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.60,0:06:46.04,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Barney! You shouldn't use this line for private use!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.04,0:06:48.77,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call you back from outside my office, so hang tight!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.48,0:06:53.60,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What? Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.93,0:06:58.18,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the bullet the lieutenant used was the one she shot me with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.40,0:07:01.44,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,I still have the hole in my right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.47,0:07:04.07,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I think we can set something up...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.07,0:07:04.48,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.34,0:07:08.44,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Barry, don't you miss going on rampages?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.57,0:07:15.25,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,Roger. I won't kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.25,0:07:17.45,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,The second passage to the warehouse district, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.14,0:07:26.67,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Breda, go find these ingredients right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.05,0:07:30.82,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Pork bones and meat, carbon, ammonia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.31,0:07:32.38,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,What's all this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.38,0:07:34.65,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to whip up a burnt corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.65,0:07:36.35,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,H-Human transmutation?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.68,0:07:38.39,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.39,0:07:41.24,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to be something that resembles a burnt corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.24,0:07:43.85,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,But if the medical examiner looks closely...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.16,0:07:47.10,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to burn it up so badly they won't even be able to have it appraised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.10,0:07:49.82,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,But what will you do if they decide to check the treatment marks on her teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.68,0:07:51.99,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It's all under control.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.02,0:07:55.12,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be able to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.59,0:08:02.46,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm no expert, but I do know enough to make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.59,0:08:05.56,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also good at transmuting burnt corpses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.21,0:08:08.04,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.99,0:08:16.97,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You're Maria Ross, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.61,0:08:23.43,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It's a dummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.89,0:08:26.98,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to die here tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.17,0:08:41.36,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't just sit there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.61,0:08:49.83,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Oww...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.15,0:09:03.06,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Fullmetal. {ep 17}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.06,0:09:05.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What's the meaning of this, Colonel?! {ep 17}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.69,0:09:07.77,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Was that the fullmetal boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.70,0:09:11.53,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,That's not good... this was unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.23,0:09:13.32,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Edward...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.32,0:09:16.21,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the Colonel will take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.32,0:09:18.20,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.04,0:09:19.89,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.88,0:09:28.25,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,While Barry was helping Ms. Ross break out of jail,\Nhe made a deal with the Young Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.90,0:09:33.97,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,And the Young Master commanded me to escort her to the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.53,0:09:38.84,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,And we promised him we'd meet here to set Second Lieutenant Ross free.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.29,0:09:40.58,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.58,0:09:42.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I still don't like it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.20,0:09:47.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It means the bastard colonel pulled a fast one on us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.13,0:09:51.47,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,It's more convincing to actually have you see her than to explain it in words, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.50,0:09:54.84,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.84,0:09:57.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The Colonel is totally right this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.62,0:09:58.98,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of the Colonel...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.37,0:10:06.00,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,I also recall him saying, "Having a pissed-off brat around the place would just be a total nuisance to the mission!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.19,0:10:08.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That damned colonel!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.00,0:10:10.44,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,What is this mission you speak of?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.44,0:10:13.50,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something else to do aside from rescuing Second Lieutenant Ross?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.70,0:10:14.76,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.76,0:10:19.05,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,We decided to fish out the mastermind hiding within the military.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.05,0:10:20.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Next time I see him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.19,0:10:22.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Fish out?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.89,0:10:27.35,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Barry, who knows the secret behind\NResearch Laboratory 5, went out and made a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.13,0:10:30.57,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,They'll definitely come to shut him up for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.78,0:10:43.24,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.72,0:10:48.75,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,So the only reason they took Ed was because he'd be a nuisance?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.05,0:10:50.50,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.66,0:10:57.61,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,And I lent them a hand in exchange for Barry telling me the secret to his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.07,0:10:59.26,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,But it turns out...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.97,0:11:04.89,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,The scientist who turned me into this is long dead, so I don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.89,0:11:07.05,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,What?! That's not fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.05,0:11:12.61,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, that Alphonse guy is kind of in the same boat as me, so why don't you try asking him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.64,0:11:16.57,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,So I decided to come to you instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.57,0:11:18.71,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,It's a promise, so I'm counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.53,0:11:24.18,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... I really don't have anything to do with that promise...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.57,0:11:27.43,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,I really have nothing to do with this, do I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.43,0:11:30.53,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Philosopher's stones... Homunculus...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.53,0:11:32.83,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why I was dragged into all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.43,0:11:38.84,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Now we have quite a bit of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.50,0:11:43.13,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,If we discover the truth behind the murder of the Brigadier General, the situation will change, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.19,0:11:47.64,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,We'll definitely prove you were falsely accused.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.24,0:11:52.30,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lieute- Brigadier General Hughes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.19,0:11:56.65,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He's really gone, isn't he...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.34,0:12:00.65,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,What do you plan to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.59,0:12:08.29,Default,Gracia,0000,0000,0000,,Move forward on the path you're content with. {ep 16}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.10,0:12:14.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We have someone who's willing to collaborate with us, even though we committed taboo...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.84,0:12:19.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We also have someone who'll scold and support us...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.07,0:12:25.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I have a younger brother who I made a promise with... to return to our bodies...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.15,0:12:29.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I also don't have anywhere to return...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.06,0:12:34.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,With that said, I have no choice but to move forward...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.25,0:12:37.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,In a way that won't cause a single death of anyone important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.66,0:12:43.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If it seems someone is going to be victimized, I'll protect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.33,0:12:48.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It may be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.18,0:12:53.83,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard enough keeping my own head, but protecting others, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.24,0:12:55.84,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It may be arrogant of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.76,0:13:00.31,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,but this is the only thing I can think of,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.13,0:13:03.79,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,so I'm going to move forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.73,0:13:17.10,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Second Lieutenant Ross, what do you plan to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.10,0:13:20.11,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,I plan to go to the country of Xing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.16,0:13:28.87,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Should I at least let your parents know?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.86,0:13:32.63,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.32,0:13:39.58,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,If it happens that information about me being alive is leaked from my parents, it'd be irreparable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.49,0:13:41.85,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.85,0:13:44.39,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Major Armstrong. Second Lieutenant Breda.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.39,0:13:45.25,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.29,0:13:48.55,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Please pass a message to Colonel Mustang for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.55,0:13:51.55,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,"I greatly appreciate you saving me."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.55,0:13:55.10,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Ask him to order me back in the case of emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.10,0:13:58.79,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,I will gladly risk my life to assist him if that ever happens!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.44,0:14:01.29,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.79,0:14:09.16,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Stay well, Edward.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.02,0:14:12.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I never got you back for that slap.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.30,0:14:14.68,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.86,0:14:26.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Maybe next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.33,0:14:30.55,Default,Fuu,0000,0000,0000,,You have good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.50,0:14:34.68,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Fu, what is Xing like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.43,0:14:40.32,Default,Fu,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pleasant country, with great food and nice people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.32,0:14:42.06,Default,Fu,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.88,0:14:47.07,Default,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,So I can expect a paradise after crossing this desert, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.71,0:14:49.01,Default,Fu,0000,0000,0000,,You sure can.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.01,0:14:53.24,Default,Fu,0000,0000,0000,,However, crossing this desert is a cruel task in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.60,0:14:54.83,Default,Fu,0000,0000,0000,,Careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.51,0:14:59.42,Default,Fu,0000,0000,0000,,You should conserve your fluids.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.64,0:15:05.93,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll drop by your store tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.93,0:15:08.26,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want as your gift, Elizabeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.25,0:15:10.98,Default,Eliza,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me, Roy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.34,0:15:13.39,Default,Eliza,0000,0000,0000,,Kate, we have customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.76,0:15:15.71,Default,Eliza,0000,0000,0000,,Could you go get Jacquelyn?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.35,0:15:19.24,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Jacquelyn, we have customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.84,0:15:21.09,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.93,0:15:33.19,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.14,0:15:35.07,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Barry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.07,0:15:36.73,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Falman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.73,0:15:39.83,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,You can't kill this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.24,0:15:51.90,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,This smell of cigarettes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.90,0:15:53.09,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Second Lieutenant Havoc?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.79,0:16:01.18,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What do you think I'm disguised for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.46,0:16:04.10,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,This is why I can't stand guys who aren't used to battles!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.10,0:16:05.73,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.73,0:16:08.52,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,You were only "dragged in".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.85,0:16:10.29,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,So don't attack him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.29,0:16:13.24,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Someone from the army could be watching us at any moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.12,0:16:17.91,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.51,0:16:23.67,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,We're heading outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.21,0:16:30.23,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,But there may be enemies outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.23,0:16:31.88,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.35,0:16:43.48,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.35,0:16:45.40,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Second Lieutenant!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.00,0:16:58.95,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, we have the hawkeye on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.31,0:17:03.50,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I just heard a loud noise. Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.50,0:17:04.75,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.69,0:17:10.09,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,The customer played a prank on Jacquelyn, so I hit him a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.09,0:17:11.42,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.60,0:17:13.92,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You're harsh, Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.46,0:17:17.93,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,All right, don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.93,0:17:20.70,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,We have a lot to ask you... er...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.70,0:17:22.81,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Does he understand what we're saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.99,0:17:25.35,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta be kidding me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.35,0:17:26.45,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.07,0:17:29.81,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,That's my body!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.81,0:17:31.82,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,What?! How could this be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.97,0:17:37.02,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,They threw in some kind of experimental animal or a soul inside my body!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.02,0:17:40.83,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,And now, he's here to get his soul back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.20,0:17:44.00,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,This brings back so many memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.00,0:17:48.16,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen it since I had my soul pulled out of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.69,0:17:55.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A transmutation circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.07,0:17:59.30,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's similar to the one I saw in Research Laboratory 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.63,0:18:02.81,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A two-headed dragon... A sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.11,0:18:06.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Agh, dammit! The top part's gone, so I can't tell anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.90,0:18:14.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Need something from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.72,0:18:16.50,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If it's money, I don't-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.82,0:18:19.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,An Ishbalan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.76,0:18:32.13,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Young lad, would you become a hostage in order for us to get our holy land back from the army?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.39,0:18:36.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way the army would give in for one kid like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.83,0:18:40.86,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The civil war began with the death of a child, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.32,0:18:45.24,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know what could be\Nthe beginning of a change in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.24,0:18:47.66,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out; this is disgraceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.79,0:18:52.37,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Shan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.37,0:18:53.92,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,You idiots...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.74,0:18:57.40,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to bring shame to the Ishbalan name?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.01,0:19:02.95,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Could you let that man go?\NHe won't try to harm you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.25,0:19:08.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you save me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.28,0:19:12.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you all hate Amestrians?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.01,0:19:18.34,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,I know that not all Amestrians are evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.96,0:19:27.16,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Both Lady Shan and I were saved by Amestrian doctors when we were badly injured during the civil war.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.16,0:19:34.48,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,In all honesty, we despise your kind, but I wouldn't be here today if it weren't for that couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.48,0:19:35.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Couple?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.48,0:19:38.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Could you be talking about the Rockbells?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.52,0:19:45.23,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You know Doctor Rockbell?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.23,0:19:46.74,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.38,0:19:51.76,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The doctor saved so many of us Ishbalans.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.54,0:19:53.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.66,0:19:57.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So Uncle and Aunt Rockbell...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.58,0:20:04.35,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,They stayed with us, despite the war getting worse and worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.85,0:20:09.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,How were their last moments?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.29,0:20:15.77,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,They were killed by an Ishbalan...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.56,0:20:19.28,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,...an Ishbalan patient they saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.67,0:20:22.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.69,0:20:25.24,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,We're so sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.29,0:20:30.82,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.71,0:20:33.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.39,0:20:36.42,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't see his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.25,0:20:40.67,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,But he was an Ishbalan with a tattoo on his right arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.43,0:20:55.54,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,When you get the chance, please convey our feelings to their gravestones.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.33,0:20:59.01,Default,Shan,0000,0000,0000,,Both our gratitude... and our apologies...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.42,0:21:19.24,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,This is just grand!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.24,0:21:24.72,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,This is like the once-in-a-lifetime chance for me to cut up my own body as much as I want!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.03,0:21:28.24,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,You told me earlier not to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.24,0:21:30.72,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,To hell with this mission!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.93,0:21:35.23,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,My soul keeps shaking... It wants to cut him up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.54,0:21:36.57,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.95,0:21:40.90,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, wouldn't the normal approach to this be wishing to go back inside your old body?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.73,0:21:44.19,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,That body won't last much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.89,0:21:47.49,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so it's rotten...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.49,0:21:49.87,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand it anymore!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.87,0:21:51.24,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to cut him up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.24,0:21:54.00,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,I get to decide what to do with my own body!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.00,0:21:56.57,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,I said, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.57,0:21:57.73,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.73,0:21:59.07,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if it's a fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.07,0:22:00.71,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like there's some trouble between her and the customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.19,0:22:04.75,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Oops, I'm going to have to call you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.51,0:22:07.47,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a customer, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.16,0:24:00.97,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,She's a strong, proud woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.97,0:24:04.63,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,A beautiful woman, loved by her comrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.63,0:24:10.88,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,But her weapon which shoots down enemies has lost its power, and her flame of life fleetingly went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.72,0:24:15.89,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.89,0:24:19.65,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 19, Death of the Undying.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.40,0:24:24.19,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,She becomes anguished.\NHer memories bring about her suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.19,0:24:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
